12/01/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR and the Office of the High Representative (OHR) reiterated on Tuesday (11 January) that there is evidence proving that war crimes suspect Ratko Mladic stayed in military facilities in Han Pijesak, Republika Srpska (RS), during the past summer. BiH Defence Ministry investigators had claimed they found no information Mladic had been at the facilities. 
In other news Tuesday, EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey met with RS President Dragan Cavic in Banja Luka. Leakey praised the implementation of defence reforms in RS but again emphasised the need for full co-operation with the UN tribunal. (Dnevni avaz - 12/01/05; RTRS, PBS BiH - 11/01/05) 
